To add new workflows we need to create a new .yml files inside the .github/workflows directory.

To use multi-line commands use "|"

Always install the software inside the runner before executing software related commands

If there are many workflows since "on: push" would trigger all the workflows we can disable the specific workflow and run the required one alone.


we can execute shell script inside the runner too. for the shell scripts to run it should have an "+x" permission always add this to your shell script inside the workflow

Parallel jobs are default when running multi-jobs pipeline to make the jobs sequential always use "needs" syntax

variables can be used on three levels namely,

 step level
 job level
 workflow level

 workflow level variables can be accessed by one workflow at a time. so if we want other workflows in the repository to access the variables
 we need to setup repository level variables

variables and secrets can be stored in github under settings and secrets and variables sections

********* variables and secrets can be stored on organizational level, repo level and environment level  **********

